  "text": "An important issue is, as recently was published by van Harten et al., that the price of several (expensive) drugs presently differs substantially between countries. This can influence the transferability of the results. The price for ipilimumab in Portugal was €2,975 per 50 mg, which means a total drug costs of €59,500, lower compared to TIL [CITATION_1] . Obviously in such case the model outcomes will be different; probably resulting in TIL being \"more costly, but more effective\" compared to ipilimumab.",
